## Code Generation Patterns

### Server Stubs

Generate route handlers and request/response types:

```bash
openapi-generator generate -i openapi.yaml -g python-fastapi -o server/
```

- Implement handler logic; do not modify generated routing
- Regenerate when spec changes; reconcile manually if needed

### Client SDKs

Generate typed clients for consumers:

```bash
openapi-generator generate -i openapi.yaml -g python -o client/
```

- Publish SDK with API releases
- Version SDK to match API version

### Validation Middleware

Use spec to validate requests and responses at runtime:

```python
# Conceptual: validate request body against schema
from openapi_core import validate_request
from openapi_core.contrib.requests import RequestsOpenAPIRequest

def validate_and_handle(request):
    openapi_request = RequestsOpenAPIRequest(request)
    validate_request(openapi_request, spec)
    return handle(request)
```

